 drank the rum went straight to sleep never woke up until 2.30pm when the offic told me to pack up as I was to go on the Instruction staff to the Train Battalion . All I said was I thank God I was so utter worn out with the cold hard work , but I soon got my thing togeth went to Head Quarter from there to E Camp where I got a new Pair of boot as I was almost bootless in rag as cloth boot seem scarc in franc at that time all my knee were bare my Tunic was all in rag , so when we got to Albert where we caught the train I got a clean cHang of undercloth but no clean tunic or Pant , so I had to come to England in Rag on reach Horseferri Road they charg me 1.0.0 for a new tunic 6/3 for a new hat , that was nice after go through what I had to have to pay for your own cloth ( nice armi this ) We arriv at the Train Battalion at Rolleston Camp Salisburi Plain was on the staff instruct recruit in the Barb wire entangl ( Rapid Wire ) was there 9 month put hundr of men through Rapid wire lesson . then my turn came again for Franc I came over again in Jan 1918 join the Battalion again at Lumbr from there we went into camp at a place not far from Nubr Gleec [ ? ] when our turn came we start in parti of Ten to go up to the trench at Plougstreet on the way up we had a rest there was a parti in front of us sit at the Road side I heard a shot fire it was one of our own men who had shot [Servic Record show he rejoin his unit in Februari ]
